the montgomery county building code ammendement requires a minimum headroom clearance of 7'ft.  The addition in questionwas designed to match a pre 1980's SFD.  The basement slams and wall heights in the addition match the existing house.  The steel beam in the basement in both the old and new sections have a head clearence of 6'6 inches.  The IRC governing most of the state of Maryland requires a miminum head clerarance under a beam in a basement to be 6ft 4'.(section R305.1.2)  The designer and builder didnot realize Montgomery County had their own requirements until the building inspector brought it to their attention. to raise the beam leave the upper floors of the addito 6' higher than the existing house.  A letter from the homeowner states that they have no problem with the 6ft 6' head height of the beam.
